The paper deals with the computation of temporal-probabilistic joins with negation, which is a topic related to databases and artificial intelligence. The paper also introduces a mechanism for lineage-aware temporal windows, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
